1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
The ground beneath you is slowly sliding on giant tectonic plates.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:08,000
These plates form Earth's lithosphere, floating on molten rock.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Can you feel it moving?

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:14,400
Mid-ocean ridges pull plates apart, while subduction zones push them down.

5
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:15,600
Imagine the pressure!

6
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:18,000
This movement causes earthquakes and volcanoes.

7
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,000
They can erupt without warning!

8
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:24,800
Understanding these forces helps us predict disasters and appreciate our dynamic planet.

9
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,600
What if the ground shifted right now?

10
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,200
Curious about our Earth?

11
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:32,400
Hit like and follow for more geological wonders!
